### Auth-Service Health Check
GET http://localhost:3002/health
Accept: application/json

### Get Auth-Service Status
GET http://localhost:3002/api/auth/status
Accept: application/json

### Wait for Password Email Events (RabbitMQ should have routed them)
### Check if credentials were created for imported users
GET http://localhost:3002/api/auth/credentials?userId=usr_test_001
Accept: application/json

### Get All Credentials (verify emails were sent)
GET http://localhost:3002/api/auth/credentials
Accept: application/json

### Verify Temporary Password Works (use password from email)
POST http://localhost:3002/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user1@test-import.com",
  "password": "TempPass123!@"
}

### Change Password on First Login (needs passwordChange flag + token from login)
POST http://localhost:3002/api/auth/change-password
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {TOKEN_FROM_LOGIN}

{
  "currentPassword": "TempPass123!@",
  "newPassword": "MySecurePassword123!@"
}

### Login with New Password
POST http://localhost:3002/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user1@test-import.com",
  "password": "MySecurePassword123!@"
}

